{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Context / Problem\n\nToday the reconciler core reaches into the Jira adapter directly: differ/apply sites call\n`outbound_fields.py`, `adf.py`, `jira_fields.py`, `comment_limits.py`, and the `acli*` cluster\nas concrete modules (ADR 0035 §(a)/§(b) inventory). There is no named interface a second\nbackend could implement. This story introduces that interface — the `Backend` facade, its role\nProtocols, and the `RemoteRef` identity type pinned in ADR 0035 §(d)\n[rebar:ef33-eaf6-a545-4bfb] — plus a backend-agnostic **contract test suite** and a thin\n`JiraBackend` that wraps today's Jira modules with **zero behavior change**. No core call sites\nare rewired here (that is S4 [rebar:6673-7636-a116-4f90]); this story only lands the port and\nits first implementation so downstream stories have something concrete to route through.\n\nEdit-set:\n- New `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/_backend.py` — the `Backend` facade, the five role\n  Protocols (`TicketTransport`, `OutboundMapper`, `InboundMapper`, `FieldSanitizer`,\n  `IdentityConvention`), the opt-in capability Protocols (`SupportsLinks`, `SupportsComments`,\n  `SupportsIncremental`), and the `RemoteRef{vendor, instance, remote_id}` dataclass.\n- New `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/adapters/jira/backend.py` — `JiraBackend`, a thin\n  wrapper delegating to the existing Jira modules (`acli.AcliClient`, `outbound_fields`,\n  `inbound_fields`/`inbound_translate`, `adapters/jira/jira_fields.py`, `comment_limits`).\n- New tests: a parameterized contract suite + an in-memory `FakeBackend` + characterization\n  tests pinning current Jira mapper outputs.\n\n## Approach\n\nDerive each Protocol's method signatures from the **de-facto surface the core already calls**,\nso `JiraBackend` is a pure delegation shim and no logic moves yet:\n- `TicketTransport` ← the create/read/update/transition/comment methods on `acli.AcliClient`.\n- `OutboundMapper` ← `outbound_fields.py`'s local→Jira field/diff mapping (+ `adf` encode).\n- `InboundMapper` ← the `inbound_*` payload→local extraction.\n- `FieldSanitizer` ← `jira_fields.py` sanitizers + `comment_limits.py` size-fit.\n- `IdentityConvention` ← the `rebar-id` label read/write convention (`rebar_id_audit.py`),\n  now expressed over `RemoteRef` instead of a bare key string.\n\nAuthor a **contract suite** parameterized over a `backend_factory` fixture and run it against\nboth `JiraBackend` (over the existing Jira subprocess/REST fakes) and `FakeBackend`. The suite\nasserts only observable contract behavior; `FakeBackend` is test-only (lives under `tests/`,\nnever shipped). This is TDD-held-out: the contract + characterization tests are authored and\nseen RED first, then `JiraBackend` is implemented to green.\n\n## Scope\n\n- The `_backend.py` port module (Protocols + capability Protocols + `RemoteRef`).\n- `JiraBackend` thin wrapper (delegation only — no field-mapping logic relocated; that is S4).\n- The contract test suite + `FakeBackend` + characterization tests.\n- **Out of scope:** rewiring any core call site (S4); the registry / config selection (S3);\n  physically moving `acli*`/`adf`/`outbound_fields`/`comment_limits` (S5); any real second\n  backend (epic `be74`).\n\n## Testing\n\n- **Tier:** unit + contract, RED-first (held-out oracle per rebar-implement).\n- **Contract suite** (backend-agnostic, run against `JiraBackend` and `FakeBackend`): outbound\n  map→inbound unmap round-trips to the same local fields the reconciler syncs; sanitizer\n  enforces label/comment limits and is idempotent; `IdentityConvention` stamps and finds a\n  `RemoteRef`; capability Protocols are honored only when advertised (`isinstance`/`hasattr`\n  gate observed via behavior, not structure).\n- **Characterization tests** pin the **exact current** outputs of the Jira mappers for\n  representative tickets, proving `JiraBackend` is behavior-preserving.\n- **Teeth:** perturb a `JiraBackend` delegation (e.g. drop the priority map) and confirm a\n  contract/characterization test goes RED, then restore.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `_backend.py` defines `Backend`, the five role Protocols, the three capability Protocols,\n  and `RemoteRef` — importable as `from rebar._engine.rebar_reconciler._backend import Backend,\n  RemoteRef` (verified by an import test).\n- [ ] `JiraBackend` implements `Backend`; the contract suite passes against it **and** against\n  `FakeBackend` (verified: `make test` green for the new suite parameterized over both).\n- [ ] Characterization tests demonstrate the Jira mapper outputs are byte-for-byte unchanged\n  from pre-story `main` for the representative fixtures (verified: tests pin literal expected\n  values captured from current behavior).\n- [ ] No core differ/apply module is modified by this story (verified: `git diff --stat` touches\n  only `_backend.py`, `adapters/jira/backend.py`, and `tests/`).\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` all green."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784695738406486001,"uuid":"e8a65e11-8366-4c81-bee5-02ed3a44490f"}